  "text": "A brief application of an MTS reagent may result in incomplete chemical modification of cysteines [CITATION_1] , but prolonged exposure increases the probability of disulfide formation, even with partially buried cysteines. The prolonged Ca v 2.1 exposure to MTSET suggests that cysteines in different sides of S6s and S5s were modified [CITATION_2] , despite the fact that some positions do not face the ion permeation pathway.",
